<key id="d0" for="node" attr.name="entity_type" attr.type="string"/>
<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="&quot;IMAGE_1&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORI_IMG"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The image captures a breathtaking natural phenomenon: a geyser erupting dramatically under a clear blue sky, with a vibrant rainbow arcing through its steam plume. In the foreground, a large, light gray or off-white geyser cone, likely composed of mineral deposits like sinter, dominates the left-center. This conical formation has a rugged, uneven texture, with steam visibly rising from its base and surrounding ground, creating a misty atmosphere close to the earth. From the top of this cone, a powerful, tall column of dense white steam erupts vertically, then billows outwards and upwards, dissipating into softer, cloud-like formations against the bright blue sky. The steam plume is thickest and most concentrated at its base, gradually becoming more diffuse as it ascends and spreads across the upper portion of the frame. Through the lighter, more dispersed part of the steam, a distinct and colorful rainbow is visible, gracefully arching from the mid-left of the steam plume down towards the right side of the frame, touching the horizon near the distant treeline. The colors of the rainbow, including red, orange, yellow, green, blue, indigo, and violet, are clearly distinguishable. The immediate ground surrounding the geyser is flat, barren, and a mixture of light brown, gray, and white tones, suggesting mineral-rich soil or dried mud, with some small, dark patches that could be water or wet areas. In the mid-ground and background, a dense forest of dark green evergreen trees stretches horizontally across the scene, forming a clear horizon line beneath the expansive, cloudless blue sky. The overall atmosphere is one of natural power and serene beauty, enhanced by the rare and captivating sight of the rainbow intersecting the geyser's steam."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_1.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;Geyser Mound&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">A large, light-colored, rocky conical formation, likely composed of mineral deposits, from which a powerful column of steam and hot water is actively erupting. Its surface is rugged and appears somewhat barren. Geyser mounds are evidence of ongoing volcanic activity, common in areas like Yellowstone National Park, where their waters are frequently near or above boiling. The crust surrounding these hydrothermal features can be thin and break easily, often overlying scalding water, making it crucial for visitors to stay on designated boardwalks and trails to ensure safety and preserve delicate formations.</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_1.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;Steam Eruption&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">A thick, white, and voluminous column of steam and hot water vapor vigorously erupting from the geyser mound, rising high into the clear blue sky and dispersing into a large cloud-like formation. These eruptions are a clear indication of ongoing volcanic activity and represent a significant hydrothermal feature. The waters involved in such eruptions are frequently near or above boiling, highlighting the powerful and potentially dangerous nature of these natural phenomena.</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_1.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;Sky&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">A clear, bright blue sky dominating the upper portion of the image, providing a vibrant backdrop to the geyser and steam. Some lighter, wispy clouds are visible, likely formed by the dispersing steam. Given that much of Yellowstone National Park, where such geysers are found, is above 7,500 feet (2,275 m), the sky often appears vast and clear, though the weather can be unpredictable.</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_1.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;Rainbow&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">A vibrant, multi-colored arc of light, displaying the spectrum of colors (red, orange, yellow, green, blue, indigo, violet), appearing within the steam plume and extending down towards the ground on the right side of the image. This natural optical phenomenon occurs when sunlight refracts through water droplets in the geyser's steam, creating a beautiful visual effect.</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_1.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;Forest&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">A dense line of dark green conifer trees, forming a natural border in the middle ground and background, stretching horizontally across the landscape behind the geyser, indicating a natural wilderness setting. In areas like Yellowstone National Park, forests provide habitat for a variety of wildlife. Visitors are cautioned to avoid areas of dead trees (snags), which may suddenly fall, especially on windy days.</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_1.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;Ground&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">The light-colored, barren, and rocky terrain in the foreground and immediately surrounding the geyser mound, characterized by mineral deposits, some scattered rocks, and possibly damp or pooled areas. In hydrothermal regions, this ground can be extremely dangerous; the crust surrounding features is often thin and breaks easily, overlying scalding water. For safety, visitors are strictly required to stay on designated boardwalks and trails to protect both themselves and the delicate geological formations.</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_1.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="Geysers &amp; Hot Springs">
  <data key="d0">IMG_ENTITY</data>
  <data key="d1">The image perfectly illustrates a geyser erupting with a rainbow, representing the 'Geysers &amp; Hot Springs' highlighted in the text as evidence of ongoing volcanic activity and a key attraction within Yellowstone National Park.</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_1.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;YELLOWSTONE NATIONAL PARK&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A prominent national park in Wyoming, serving as the main location for various activities, camping, and pass usage described in the text. Its visitor access in winter is under review, and it experiences distinct seasonal weather patterns."&lt;SEP&gt;"Yellowstone National Park is a large national park, mostly above 7,500 feet (2,275 m), known for unpredictable weather, busy roads, dangerous hydrothermal features, and diverse wildlife. This document is a trip planner for the park in 2010."&lt;SEP&gt;"Yellowstone National Park is a major national park primarily located in Wyoming, with parts extending into Montana and Idaho, known for its various features, roads, and visitor activities. It is also referred to as a destination for inquiries regarding authorized providers."&lt;SEP&gt;"Yellowstone National Park is the primary organization managing the park, providing services, setting regulations, and offering various facilities and activities. It also refers to the geographical area itself."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-47639910c915bafe8d80a13752ccb8ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b3cdc79954b41510d5ae0999ef6daf3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-88e5c2ce20f231e3a806b09b6cab2c4d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7351b12b3e5ac87b530aa3bf02ecf8cc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COAST GUARD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Coast Guard is a government organization whose approved 'wearable' personal flotation devices are required for each person boating."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e22ff6904de7a8eef70b8467d191a104</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;XANTERRA PARKS AND RESORTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"An organization that handles reservations for Yellowstone National Park, providing contact information including a P.O. Box and phone numbers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4c35ba44e693c85e6206ade502e115d5</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MAMMOTH HOT SPRINGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A specific location within Yellowstone National Park known for its geothermal features and a visitor center."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8f0e2c09fcd8882a570819d4a5395ca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NORRIS GEYSER BASIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A specific location within Yellowstone National Park known for its geothermal features and a museum."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8f0e2c09fcd8882a570819d4a5395ca3</data>
</node>
